  "description": "Growing protocol for *Claytonia perfoliata*, native to western North America. Cool-season, shade-tolerant annual suited to spring and fall production in temperate climates. Prefers moist, peaty soil and partial shade; self-seeds readily. 37–40 days to maturity; minimal pest pressure.",
